source.description: Financial Industry Business Ontology (FIBO) - Production T-Box only (schema) from EDM Council

entities.name: Account
entities.description: container for records associated with a business arrangement for regular transactions and services

entities.name: AccountingFramework
entities.description: framework, including policies, methods, rules, and processes, used to measure, recognize, present, and disclose the information appearing in an entity's financial statements, and, from a legal ownership perspective, that is applied for accounting consolidation determination

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: AccountOwnership
entities.description: holding of an account

description._: event announced, initiated or carried out by an organization that affects a legal entity or the securities it issues and may have a material impact on that entity's stakeholders, such as shareholders and creditors

entities.name: ActionClassificationScheme
entities.description: scheme for classifying the kinds of actions and events that may be announced, initiated or carried out by an organization that affects a legal entity or the securities it issues

description._: classifier that distinguishes the kinds of actions and events that may be announced, initiated or carried out by an organization that affects a legal entity or the securities it issues, such as income-oriented events

entities.name: Adult
entities.description: person who has attained the age of majority as defined in some jurisdiction

entities.name: Affiliate
entities.description: party that is related to a legal entity, directly, or indirectly through one or more intermediaries, and controls, or is controlled by, or is under common control with that entity, typically determined by the degree of ownership

entities.name: AgencyAgreement
entities.description: agreement that designates a party as a registered agent to represent and act on behalf of another party in some, typically legal, financial, or medical capacity

entities.name: AgentForServiceOfProcess
entities.description: registered agent (person or organization) designated by a business entity, such as a corporation, to receive legal correspondence on behalf of the business entity in the jurisdiction in which the agent's address is located

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Agreement
entities.description: negotiated understanding between two or more parties, reflecting the offer and acceptance of commitments on the part of either party

entities.name: ArticlesOfIncorporation
entities.description: contract that establishes a new corporation or, when amended, adjusts the legal basis for the corporation, and outlines basic information about the corporation, including the type of business, and a description of the business' operational characteristics

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Association
entities.description: not-for-profit organization that is owned by and acts on behalf of its members

entities.name: Auditor
entities.description: party qualified and authorized to review and verify the accuracy of financial records and ensure that companies comply with tax laws

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: BankingProduct
entities.description: product provided to consumers and businesses by a depository institution

entities.name: Basket
entities.description: collection of goods, services, or other things (e.g., financial contracts) that can be purchased and sold in some marketplace

entities.name: BeneficialOwner
entities.description: party that enjoys the benefits of ownership (such as receipt of income) of something even though its ownership (title) may be in the name of another party (called a nominee or registered owner)

entities.name: BeneficialOwnership
entities.description: control situation linking something at least one beneficial owner

entities.name: BilateralAgreement
entities.description: agreement where two parties commit to perform specific actions or obligations towards each other

entities.name: BoardAgreement
entities.description: formal, legally binding agreement between members of the Board of Directors of the organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: BoardCompositionControl
entities.description: situation in which a voting shareholder, entity owner, or some other party in the case of a not-for-profit organization, appoints and/or nominates someone to the board of directors of an organization for some period of time

entities.name: BoardMember
entities.description: party that has fiduciary responsibility with respect to the organization, including but not limited to determining and executing corporate policy

entities.name: BoardMembership
entities.description: situation relating an individual member of the board of directors to the organization

entities.name: BoardOfDirectors
entities.description: group of people comprising the governing body of an organization that has the authority to set organizational strategy and policies as well as to select and, to some degree manage, leadership

entities.name: Branch
entities.description: part of a larger organization that might not be co-located with it

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: BrokerageAccount
entities.description: account offered by a broker that allows the investor to deposit funds and place investment orders

entities.name: BrokerageFirm
entities.description: firm in the business of buying and selling securities, operating as both a broker and a dealer, depending on the transaction

entities.name: BrokerDealer
entities.description: any party in the business of buying and selling securities, operating as both a broker and a dealer, depending on the transaction

entities.name: BusinessCalendar
entities.description: schedule and communications tool used to manage meetings, plan events, and coordinate activities within and/or across organizations

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: BusinessCenter
entities.description: BusinessCenter as defined in OWL ontology

entities.name: BusinessCenterCodeScheme
entities.description: coding scheme used to define a set of codes for municipalities or business centers

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: BusinessDayAdjustment
entities.description: BusinessDayAdjustment as defined in OWL ontology

entities.name: BusinessEntity
entities.description: entity that is formed and administered as per commercial law in order to engage in business activities

entities.name: BusinessIdentifierCode
entities.description: international identifier for financial and non-financial institutions used to facilitate automated processing of information for financial services

entities.name: BusinessIdentifierCodeScheme
entities.description: scheme that specifies the elements of a unique business identifier code (BIC) scheme to identify financial and non-financial institutions used to facilitate automated processing of information for financial services

entities.name: BusinessPartyPrefix
entities.description: four-character (4 alphanumeric) code associated with an organization for the purposes of banking telecommunications

entities.name: BusinessPartySuffix
entities.description: two-character (2 alphanumeric) code associated with the organization for the purposes of banking telecommunications

entities.name: BusinessRegisterIdentifier
entities.description: identifier that uniquely identifies a business register, such as a register identified by the Global Legal Entity Identifier Foundation (GLEIF) registration authorities list

entities.name: BusinessRegistry
entities.description: registry for registering and maintaining information about business entities

entities.name: BusinessRegistryEntry
entities.description: entry in a business registry

description._: classifier of corporate actions that involve improving liquidity or changing the overall structure of the organization through diversification, combining and closing parts of the business, etc, to increase long-term profitability

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Buyer
entities.description: party that purchases something in exchange for money or other consideration under a contract of sale

entities.name: Bylaws
entities.description: written rules for conduct of a corporation, association, partnership or any organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Calculation
entities.description: actual execution of some computation, computational process, or operation that was scheduled or triggered by something

entities.name: CapitalLease
entities.description: lease that must be reflected on an organization's balance sheet as an asset and as a corresponding liability

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: structured product that participates in the performance of a financial asset, such as a stock, fund or index, while protecting the investor's capital

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: CapitalSurplus
entities.description: capital contributed in excess of the par value (stated value) of the ownership interest issued

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: CharteredLegalPerson
entities.description: a legal person created by a royal charter or decree

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ChiefExecutiveOfficer
entities.description: top corporate officer responsible for an organization's overall operations and performance

entities.name: ChiefFinancialOfficer
entities.description: senior-most corporate officer responsible for financial control and planning for an organization or project

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ClearingService
entities.description: service provided on behalf of an institutional market participant by a clearing services provider following a trade that finalizes the transfer of security ownership

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: CollateralAgreement
entities.description: written contract related to another contract designed to provide clarity and additional protection for all parties involved, that is separate from the primary contract and that can be independently enforced

entities.name: CommercialLendingService
entities.description: service involving the extension of credit to support business activities

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Commitment
entities.description: promise made by some party to act or refrain from acting in some manner

entities.name: CommitmentAtLarge
entities.description: commitment made by some party without direct involvement from the potential beneficiaries of that commitment

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: CommodityInstrument
entities.description: financial instrument representing an ownership interest in bulk goods, such as raw materials and primary agricultural products

entities.name: CommonInterestDevelopmentCorporation
entities.description: not-for-profit corporation set up under specific state legislation as a business entity for homeowners' associations

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: CompanyLaw
entities.description: legislation under which the formation, registration or incorporation, governance, and dissolution of a firm is administered and controlled

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: CompanySecretary
entities.description: corporate officer appointed by the directors of an organization, responsible for ensuring compliance with legal obligations related to corporate governance

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ConstitutionalOwner
entities.description: entity owner that holds an equity stake in said entity, in the form of shareholders' equity

entities.name: ConsumerFinanceCompany
entities.description: finance company that lends to individuals under the small loans laws of the jurisdiction in which they operate

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Contract
entities.description: voluntary, deliberate agreement between competent parties to which the parties agree to be legally bound, and for which the parties provide valuable consideration

entities.name: ContractLifecycle
entities.description: lifecycle of an agreement, including, but not limited to a credit agreement, financial instrument, or other formal contract, from initial stages through retirement

entities.name: ContractLifecycleEvent
entities.description: kind of event that occurs during one or more stages of the lifecycle of an agreement

entities.name: ContractLifecycleStage
entities.description: phase in the lifecycle of an agreement

entities.name: ContractParty
entities.description: legally competent party that has entered into a binding agreement, accepting and conceding obligations, responsibilities, and benefits as specified

entities.name: ContractThirdParty
entities.description: party that is indirectly involved in, but not a counterparty to, an agreement

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ContractualCommitment
entities.description: provision specifying something that the contracting parties agree to, i.e., a promise or pledge made by one of the parties to perform some action or fulfill some duty

entities.name: ContractualElement
entities.description: element, such as an arrangement, provision, requirement, rule, specification, and standard that forms an integral part of an agreement

entities.name: ContractuallyCapableEntity
entities.description: a unique entity that is legally or financially responsible for the performance of financial transactions, or has the legal right in its jurisdiction to enter independently into legal contracts, regardless of whether it is incorporated or constituted in some other way (e.g. trust, partnership, contractual). This excludes natural persons, but includes governmental organizations and supranationals.

entities.name: ContractualProduct
entities.description: product that takes the form of an agreement

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ControlledParty
entities.description: person or organization over which some party exercises some form of authority or influence with respect to some situation

entities.name: ControllingEquity
entities.description: shareholders's equity that formally confers control in the entity, either by law or as explicitly stated in a corresponding equity instrument

entities.name: CooperativeSociety
entities.description: organization owned by and operated for the benefit of those using its services

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: CorporateBylaws
entities.description: written rules for conduct of a corporation, adopted by the board of directors

entities.name: CorporateOfficer
entities.description: high-level management executive of a corporation or other organization, hired by the board of directors or the business owner(s), charged with certain operational responsibilities, and who has the authority to act on behalf of the organization, including the authority to enter into contracts on behalf of the organization

entities.name: Corporation
entities.description: formal organization that is a legal entity (artificial person) distinct from its owners, created under the jurisdiction of the laws of a state or nation

entities.name: Counterparty
entities.description: party to a contract with whom one negotiates on a given agreement

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: CRDCreditInstitution
entities.description: an undertaking whose business is to receive deposits or other repayable funds from the public and to grant credits for its own account as defined by the European Banking Authority (EBA)

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: CreditAgreementRepaidPeriodically
entities.description: credit agreement in which the principal and accrued interest may be periodically repaid or exchanged

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: party that benefits from the collateral or guarantee established under the agreement, i.e., that is protected against counterparty credit risk because the collateral or guarantee serves as security for the obligation(s) owed to them

event signifying a sudden change in credit standing, such as bankruptcy or a violation of a bond indenture or loan agreement, that raises doubts about the party's ability to meet current or future obligations

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: basket of securities whose constituents are credit agreements that allow the borrower to periodically take out money over an extended period of time rather than reapplying for a loan every time they need funds

entities.name: CreditInstitution
entities.description: an undertaking the business of which is to take deposits or other repayable funds from the public and to grant credits for its own account, and to which authorisation has been granted to operate within the European Union and European Economic Area countries (EEA)

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: CreditUnion
entities.description: not-for-profit depository institution that makes personal loans and offers other consumer banking services, organized for the purpose of promoting thrift among its members and creating a source of credit for provident or productive purposes

description._: agreement to deliver and settle a given amount of money in one currency, in exchange for a given amount in another currency at an agreed rate of exchange
agreement to deliver and settle a given amount of money in one currency, in exchange for a given amount in another currency, at an agreed date in the future and at an agreed rate of exchange
futures contract whose underlying asset is an agreement to exchange a specified amount of one currency for another at some point in the future based on pricing stated in the contract

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: foreign exchange agreement between two parties to exchange a given amount of one currency for another currency for spot delivery or for forward delivery at an agreed rate after a specified period of time

entities.name: DayCountConvention
entities.description: a business recurrence interval convention that is used to calculate the number of days in an interest payment, which applies to the amount of accrued interest or the present value for debt instruments

entities.name: Dealer
entities.description: any party that purchases goods or services for resale and acts on their own behalf in a transaction

entities.name: DebtTerms
entities.description: contract terms that specify the formal rights and obligations of borrower and lender under a contract in which funds are lent from the one party to the other

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: DemandDepositAccount
entities.description: non-interest-bearing deposit account in which deposits are payable immediately on demand, or that are issued with an original maturity or required notice period of less than seven days, or that represent funds for which the depository institution does not reserve the right to require at least seven days' written notice of an intended withdrawal

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: addendum to the master agreement that governs the exchange of collateral between parties in derivatives transactions
master agreement covering derivatives transactions to be carried out between the parties to this contract

entities.name: DirectConsolidation
entities.description: direct ownership of an entity recorded as accounting consolidation

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: corporate action involving a request for holders or beneficial owners to disclose their name, location and holdings of any issue to the issuer

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: corporate action involving the sales of subsidiary business interests or investments

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Division
entities.description: part of an organization, such as a line of business, that may have separate accounting and reporting requirements

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: DomesticUltimateParent
entities.description: party that is recognized as the ultimate parent of a given organization within the country or jurisdiction of incorporation or organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: DriversLicense
entities.description: an official document which states that a person may operate a motorized vehicle, such as a motorcycle, car, truck or a bus, on a public roadway or provides official identifying information for a non-driver

entities.name: EmancipatedMinor
entities.description: a minor who is allowed to conduct a business or any other occupation on his or her own behalf or for their own account outside the control of a parent or guardian

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: EntityLegalFormRegistry
entities.description: registry for registering and maintaining information about the legal forms that are valid for business entities for a particular jurisdiction following the ISO 20275 standard

entities.name: EntityOwner
entities.description: owner (person, group of people, or other business entity) that owns, or holds an ownership interest in, a formal business organization

entities.name: EntityOwnership
entities.description: ownership by some party of an interest in some non-governmental formal organization

description._: credit event that applies to a given legal person

entities.name: EquityInstrument
entities.description: financial instrument representing an ownership interest in an entity or pool of assets

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Executive
entities.description: person appointed and given the responsibility to manage the affairs of an organization and the authority to make decisions within specified role-specific boundaries

entities.name: ExecutiveBoardMember
entities.description: member of a board of directors that is also an employee of the organization

entities.name: ExplicitContractEventSchedule
entities.description: schedule of events, including but not limited to payment events, rate reset events and others that will occur over the lifetime of the credit agreement

entities.name: Exposure
entities.description: the extent to which an individual or organization is unprotected and open to damage, danger, risk of suffering a loss, or uncertainty

entities.name: FaceAmountCertificateCompany
entities.description: investment company which is engaged or proposes to engage in the business of issuing face-amount certificates of the installment type, or which has been engaged in such business and has any such certificate outstanding

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: FamilyOffice
entities.description: organization that assumes the day-to-day administration and management of a family's affairs

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: FinanceCompany
entities.description: financial intermediary in the business of making loans that obtains its financing from banks, institutions, and other money market sources rather than from deposits

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: FinancialExposure
entities.description: the extent to which an individual or organization is open to risk of suffering a loss in a transaction, or with respect to some investment or set of investments, e.g., some holding; the amount one stands to lose in that transaction or investment

entities.name: FinancialInstitution
entities.description: financial service provider identified as either a government agency or privately owned entity that collects funds from the public and from other institutions, and invests those funds in financial assets, such as loans, securities, bank deposits, and income-generating property

entities.name: FinancialProduct
entities.description: product provided to consumers and businesses by financial institutions such as banks, insurance companies, brokerage firms, consumer finance companies, and investment companies

entities.name: FinancialService
entities.description: service provided to consumers and businesses by financial institutions such as banks, insurance companies, brokerage firms, consumer finance companies, and investment companies

entities.name: FinancialServiceProvider
entities.description: functional entity either licensed to provide financial services to consumers and/or businesses or established by law to provide financial services, such as a central bank

description._: cashflow expression specifying the arguments required to calculate the best projected price at which the lookback option may be exercised

entities.name: ForeignBranchOwnership
entities.description: ownership by some party of some formal organization or organizational sub-unit that is a foreign affiliate and legally part of the owning entity

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

description._: product-specific master agreement intended to reflect best market practice and to provide a standard agreement for participants in the foreign exchange markets

entities.name: FormalOrganization
entities.description: FormalOrganization as defined in OWL ontology

entities.name: ForProfitCorporation
entities.description: corporation whose objective is to make money, i.e., to ensure realization of a financial benefit such that the amount of revenue gained from a business activity exceeds the expenses, costs and taxes needed to sustain that activity

entities.name: ForwardRateAgreement
entities.description: ForwardRateAgreement as defined in OWL ontology

entities.name: Funds
entities.description: artificial currency used as calculation basis for another currency(s) and accounting purposes

description._: basket of debt instruments that provides additional capacity for potential funding and does not require the proceeds to be used for any particular purpose

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: GeneralPartner
entities.description: partner and part-owner that is responsible for managing the day to day operations of the partnership and that may be jointly and severally liable for the obligations of the partnership

entities.name: GeneralPartnership
entities.description: partnership that has at least two general partners that agree to share in all assets, profits, and financial and legal liabilities of the business

entities.name: GlobalUltimateParent
entities.description: party that is recognized as the ultimate parent of a given organization world-wide

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: GovernmentAgency
entities.description: permanent or semi-permanent organization, often an appointed commission, in the machinery of government that is responsible for the oversight and administration of specific functions

entities.name: GovernmentBody
entities.description: formal organization that is an agency, instrumentality, or other body of a supranational, national, federal, state, or local government, including certain multijurisdictional agencies and departments that carry out the business of government

entities.name: GovernmentDepartment
entities.description: specialized organization responsible for a sector of government public administration

entities.name: GovernmentIssuedLicense
entities.description: grant of permission needed to legally perform some task, provide some service, exercise a certain privilege, or pursue some business or occupation

entities.name: GovernmentOfficial
entities.description: person elected or appointed to administer some aspect of a government

entities.name: Guaranty
entities.description: commitment whereby something is formally assured if a party with primary liability fails to perform

entities.name: Holding
entities.description: real or personal property (assets), including but not limited to financial assets, to which one holds title and of which one has possession

entities.name: HoldingCompany
entities.description: business entity established to own stock in another company, typically to own enough voting shares to have some level of control over that company's policies and management

description._: basket of credit facilities whose constituents are extensible, allowing companies to borrow an additional term loan or revolving credit facility (or increase the commitments applicable thereto) under the same credit agreement subject to certain parameters

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: IndividualUnilateralCommitment
entities.description: IndividualUnilateralCommitment as defined in OWL ontology

entities.name: IndustrySectorClassificationScheme
entities.description: system for allocating classifiers to organizations by industry sector

entities.name: IndustrySectorClassifier
entities.description: standardized classification or delineation for an organization, or possibly for a security representing an interest in a given organization, per some scheme for such delineation, by industry

description._: default event involving non-payment of several installment payments as scheduled in the terms of the agreement, or non-payment of a call by the beneficial owner

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Instrumentality
entities.description: organization that serves a public purpose and is closely tied to a government, but is not a government agency

entities.name: InsuranceCompany
entities.description: non-depository institution whose primary and predominant business activity is the writing of insurance or the reinsuring of risks underwritten by insurance companies, and that provides compensation based on the happening of at least one contingency

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: InsurancePolicy
entities.description: contract that (1) puts an indemnity cover into effect, (2) serves as a legal evidence of the insurance agreement, (3) sets out the exact terms on which the indemnity cover has been provided, and (4) states associated information such as the (a) specific risks and perils covered, (b) duration of coverage, (c) amount of premium, (d) mode of premium payment, and (e) deductibles, if any

entities.name: InvestmentAccount
entities.description: account that provides a record of deposits of funds and/or securities held at a financial institution

entities.name: InvestmentCompany
entities.description: any issuer which: (a) is or holds itself out as being engaged primarily, or proposes to engage primarily, in the business of investing, reinvesting, or trading in securities; (b) is engaged or proposes to engage in the business of issuing face-amount certificates of the installment type, or has been engaged in such business and has any such certificate outstanding; or (c) is engaged or proposes to engage in the business of investing, reinvesting, owning, holding, or trading in securities, and owns or proposes to acquire investment securities having a value exceeding 40 per centum of the value of such issuer's total assets (exclusive of Government securities and cash items) on an unconsolidated basis

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: InvestmentEquity
entities.description: equity that represents an ownership interest in some entity, but may or may not take the form of shareholders's equity

entities.name: InvestmentFirm
entities.description: any legal person whose regular occupation or business is the provision of one or more investment services to third parties and/or the performance of one or more investment activities on a professional basis

entities.name: InvestmentOrDepositAccount
entities.description: account associated with a product or service that requires the account holder to provide funds for management by the account provider

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: InvestmentService
entities.description: financial service designed to assist investors in using capital to create more money, either through income-producing vehicles or through more risk-oriented ventures to result in capital gains, including but not limited to providing investment advice, asset and portfolio management, and brokerage services

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Investor
entities.description: party that owns some stake in some organization by way of investment

entities.name: JointControllingParty
entities.description: party that collectively has the authority to control the affairs of some business organization

entities.name: JointStockCompany
entities.description: for-profit, unincorporated business that has some characteristics of a corporation and some features of a partnership, with ownership interests represented by shares of stock

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Judiciary
entities.description: branch of government that comprises the system of courts that interprets and applies the law in the name of the supranational, national, federal, or regional government, depending on its jurisdiction

entities.name: Lease
entities.description: credit agreement permitting the use of real estate, equipment or another asset, such as a vehicle, by the owner of that asset (the lessor) to a user (the lessee) for a specific period of time in return for payment as specified in the agreement

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: LegalAge
entities.description: age at which someone acquires the capacity to do something that they were prohibited from doing before under the law in some jurisdiction

entities.name: LegalEntityIdentifierRegistry
entities.description: registry for registering and maintaining information about business entities for a particular jurisdiction

description._: corporate action indicating a modification of the legal form of the organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: LegallyCapableAdult
entities.description: person who has attained the age of majority as defined in some jurisdiction and who is allowed to conduct a business or any other occupation on his or her own behalf or for their own account

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: LegallyCompetentNaturalPerson
entities.description: person who is considered competent, under the circumstances, to enter into a contract, conduct business, or participate in other activities that generally require the mental ability to understand problems and make decisions on his or her own behalf

entities.name: LegalWorkingAgePerson
entities.description: person whose age is greater than the minimum legal working age specified in a jurisdiction in which they work

entities.name: Legislature
entities.description: the law-making body of a political unit, usually a national government, that has power to enact, amend, and repeal public policy

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: LEIRegisteredEntity
entities.description: a legal person that has registered for and is identified by a legal entity identifier

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Lifecycle
entities.description: arrangement that compares the cyclical nature of families, organizations, processes, products, marketing, and order management, portfolio management or other systems with the cradle to grave life stages (birth, growth, maturity, decay, and death) of living organisms

entities.name: LimitedLiabilityCompanyMember
entities.description: owner of an interest in a limited liability company

description._: corporate action related to winding up a business, including but not limited to distribution of cash, assets, or both

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: LivingTrust
entities.description: trust created during an individual's lifetime where a designated person, the trustee, is given responsibility for managing that individual's assets for the benefit of the eventual beneficiary

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: MajorityControllingParty
entities.description: controlling party that possesses, either directly or indirectly, the power to direct or cause the direction of the management and policies of a legal person, whether through the ownership of a majority of voting securities, by contract, or otherwise

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ManagementCompany
entities.description: investment company that sells and manages a portfolio of securities other than a face-amount certificate company or unit investment fund

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ManagerManagedLimitedLiabilityCompany
entities.description: limited liability company in which the members appoint one or more managers to handle the daily operations and administrative responsibilities of the organization

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: ManagingMember
entities.description: owner of an interest in a limited liability company who also runs the day-to-day business operations

entities.name: MerchantService
entities.description: financial service provided by a financial institution to a merchant or other business, including but not limited to managing financial transactions via a secure channel

parentClass.description: Parent class in the inheritance hierarchy

entities.name: Minor
entities.description: a person under a certain age, usually the age of majority in a given jurisdiction, which legally demarcates childhood from adulthood
